# Trunk-based Git Workflow

`main` is the trunk. Keep it buildable and always integrate through pull requests.

## Required flow

1. `git fetch origin` and branch from up-to-date `main`:
   - `git checkout main && git pull origin main`
   - `git checkout -b feat/short-name` (or `fix/`, `chore/`)
2. Commit on the branch only.
3. `git push -u origin <branch>` — **never** `git push origin main`.
4. Open a PR: `gh pr create --base main --head <branch>`.
5. Merge with `gh pr merge` (merge commit or squash per PR; default to merge when history matters).
6. Delete the branch after merge; sync local trunk: `git checkout main && git pull origin main`.

## Branch naming

- `feat/` — features
- `fix/` — bug fixes  
- `chore/` — docs, tooling, CI, rules

## Scope

- One logical change per PR when practical.
- Short-lived branches; do not accumulate long-running feature branches on the trunk.

See [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) for contributor-facing details.
